In a speech delivered in the East Room of the White House, President Biden thanked those involved in passing the Inflation Reduction Act and highlighted the achievements of his economic plan. He emphasized the creation of over 13 million new jobs since he took office, the growth of the manufacturing sector, and the reduction of unemployment and inflation rates. Biden also discussed the impact of the law on addressing climate change, boosting clean energy jobs, and increasing America's energy security. He highlighted the provisions of the law that lower healthcare costs, allow Medicare to negotiate lower drug prices, and ensure that billionaires and big corporations pay their fair share of taxes. The President expressed optimism about America's future and emphasized the importance of unity and hard work in achieving the country's goals.